<response><error><![CDATA[OK]]></error><limit>1</limit><offset>0</offset><number_of_page_results>1</number_of_page_results><number_of_total_results>1</number_of_total_results><status_code>1</status_code><results><aliases/><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/character/3005-662/]]></api_detail_url><birthday/><date_added>2008-07-21 01:21:34</date_added><date_last_updated>2013-02-04 14:56:27</date_last_updated><deck><![CDATA[Nero is one of the main playable characters in Devil May Cry 4 alongside Dante.]]></deck><description><![CDATA[<h2><span>Overview</span></h2><p>Nero's origin remains unknown. He was raised in the city of <a data-ref-id="3035-1038" href="/fortuna/3035-1038/" slug="fortuna">Fortuna</a> as an orphan and is later taken in by <a data-ref-id="3005-2903" href="/kyrie/3005-2903/" slug="kyrie">Kyrie's</a> and <a data-ref-id="3005-4580" href="/credo/3005-4580/" slug="credo">Credo's</a> family.</p><p>He often acts sarcastic, rebellious and rather antisocial, as he likes going alone on special missions and shows an adverse attitude towards the ceremony of the Order of the Sword, even though he is one of their Holy Knights. The Order worships <a data-ref-id="3005-3258" href="/sparda/3005-3258/" slug="sparda">Sparda</a> and wants to protect the world from demons.</p><p>Nero falls in love with <a data-ref-id="3005-2903" href="/kyrie/3005-2903/" slug="kyrie">Kyrie</a> some time prior to the events of the game, and this love plays a crucial part in the plot. He is generally an emotinal person, as he is seen crying and getting very angry during the events of <a data-ref-id="3030-6681" href="/devil-may-cry-4/3030-6681/" slug="devil-may-cry-4">Devil May Cry 4</a>.</p><p>Nero wields the weapons <a data-ref-id="3055-192" href="/blue-rose/3055-192/" slug="blue-rose">Blue Rose</a>, <a data-ref-id="3055-112" href="/red-queen-sword/3055-112/" slug="red-queen-sword">Red Queen</a>, and <a data-ref-id="3055-4777" href="/devil-bringer/3055-4777/" slug="devil-bringer">Devil Bringer</a>. He later receives <a data-ref-id="3055-935" href="/yamato/3055-935/" slug="yamato">Yamato</a>, a sword that once belonged to <a data-ref-id="3005-309" href="/dante/3005-309/" slug="dante">Dante's</a> brother, <a data-ref-id="3005-1804" href="/vergil/3005-1804/" slug="vergil">Vergil</a>.</p><p>As he wants to give <a data-ref-id="3055-935" href="/yamato/3055-935/" slug="yamato">Yamato</a> to <a data-ref-id="3005-309" href="/dante/3005-309/" slug="dante">Dante</a>, the latter tells him to keep it, as it "stays in the family". This remark cemented the theory that Nero is actually an incarnation of <a data-ref-id="3005-1804" href="/vergil/3005-1804/" slug="vergil">Vergil</a>, but this has never been officially confirmed. Instead, it was hinted in the DMC 4 novel that Nero is <a data-ref-id="3005-1804" href="/vergil/3005-1804/" slug="vergil">Vergils</a> son, which has been allegedly confirmed by one of the <a data-ref-id="3010-367" href="/capcom/3010-367/" slug="capcom">Capcom</a> employees.</p><h2>Trivia</h2><p>In <a data-ref-id="3030-30944" href="/marvel-vs-capcom-3-fate-of-two-worlds/3030-30944/" slug="marvel-vs-capcom-3-fate-of-two-worlds">Marvel Vs. Capcom 3</a> when <a data-ref-id="3005-1472" href="/deadpool/3005-1472/" slug="deadpool">Deadpool</a> beats Dante, Deadpool taunts him by saying that Nero should do his fighting for him.</p>]]></description><gender>1</gender><id>662</id><image><icon_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/square_avatar/0/9747/427487-nero18.png]]></icon_url><medium_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/0/9747/427487-nero18.png]]></medium_url><screen_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/screen_medium/0/9747/427487-nero18.png]]></screen_url><small_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/9747/427487-nero18.png]]></small_url><super_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_large/0/9747/427487-nero18.png]]></super_url><thumb_url><![CDATA[h